<h2>Buttons</h2>

<h3 class="uBorderTop2" id="primary-actions">Primary actions</h3>



<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <div class="form-group">
            <label class="control-label" for="exampleInputName">Input</label>
            <input type="test" class="form-control" id="exampleInputName">
        </div>
        <div class="pull-right">
            <button class="btn btn-primary">Primary action</button>
            <button class="btn btn-default">Secondary action</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-1">
        <ul>
            <li>Reset, Cancel, and Go Back are secondary actions: Avoid using secondary actions if possible.</li>
            <li>Save, Continue, and Submit are primary actions: directly responsible for task completion.</li>
            <li>Ensure a clear visual distinction between primary and secondary actions with the classes <code>btn-default</code> and <code>btn-primary</code>.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>


<h3 class="uBorderTop2" id="primary-actions">Button order</h3>

<div class="guiExample">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6">
            <div class="form-group">
                <label class="control-label" for="exampleInputName">Input</label>
                <input type="test" class="form-control" id="exampleInputName">
            </div>
            <div class="pull-right">
                <button class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
                <button class="btn btn-default">Cancel</button>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-1">
            <ul>
                <li>Buttons are sorted by importance from left to right.</li>
                <li>Buttons should be ordered with the primary action first in the tab order.</li>
                <li>Buttons should be aligned with a formâ€™s input elements to provide a clear path to completion &mdash; this helps people complete forms faster.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3 class="uBorderTop2" id="primary-actions">Button labels</h3>
<div class="guiExample">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6">
            <div class="uMarginBs">
                <button class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
                <button class="btn btn-primary">Update</button>
                <button class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
                <button class="btn btn-primary">Apply</button>
                <button class="btn btn-primary">OK</button>
            </div>
            <div>
                <button class="btn btn-default">Cancel</button>
                <button class="btn btn-default">Reset</button>
                <button class="btn btn-default">Clear</button>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-1">
            <ul>
                <li>All button labels should be written in <strong>sentence case</strong> except for "OK" which should be uppercase.</li> 
                <li>Button labels should be as short as possible and clearly explain the action.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

